{{EngvarB|date=September 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} {{lowercase title}} {{Infobox award | name = albert sustainable production certification | current_awards = | image = File:Albert sustainable production certification logo.png | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | description = Achievements in reduction of carbon emissions | presenter = [[BAFTA]] | host = | location = London | country = United Kingdom | reward = | year2 = | holder = | website ={{url|wearealbert.org}} | network = | runtime = | ratings = | previous = | main = | next = }} '''albert sustainable production certification''' (also known as '''albert+''') is a certification for a television production's efforts to reduce its carbon footprint.<ref name="Certification">{{cite web|title=albert certification|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/responsibility/environment/albert-plus|publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref><ref name="BAFTA">{{cite web|title=BAFTA's Sustainability Efforts|url=http://www.bafta.org/about/sustainability|publisher=[[BAFTA]]|accessdate=30 March 2017}}</ref> As a result, they can display the albert sustainable production logo at the end of their credits.<ref name="Certification"/><ref>{{cite web|last1=Matthews|first1=Aaron|title=BBC, ITV and Sky get green kick up the arts with new sustainability mark|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/blog/2014/oct/28/tv-bbc-itv-sky-sustainability-mark-carbon-albert|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=30 March 2017|date=28 October 2014}}</ref>
In 2010, the [[BBC]] created a [[carbon footprint]] calculator for TV programmes, called albert. The impact of productions on the environment was recorded but the findings could not help to reduce the impact. Therefore, albert+ was created by the [[BAFTA]] albert Consortium, the industry sustainability group, as a way to encourage productions to divert waste from landfill, engage senior leaders and address energy efficiency.
==Productions with this certification== Productions that meet a criteria for sustainability are awarded one, two or three stars.
